```cpp
#include <hexi/hexi.h>
#include <vector>
#include <string>
#include <cstdint>

struct NetworkPacket {
    uint32_t packet_id;
    std::string username;
    std::vector<uint32_t> scores;
    std::string metadata;

    void serialise(auto& stream) {
        // Write packet_id (POD type)
        stream << packet_id;

        // Write username with length prefix using prefixed adaptor
        stream << hexi::prefixed(username);

        // Write scores count + scores using prefixed adaptor
        stream << hexi::prefixed(scores);

        // Write metadata as null-terminated string using null_terminated adaptor
        stream << hexi::null_terminated(metadata);
    }
};

std::vector<uint8_t> serialize_packet(const NetworkPacket& packet) {
    // Create a buffer_adaptor for std::vector<uint8_t>
    std::vector<uint8_t> buffer;
    hexi::buffer_adaptor<std::vector<uint8_t>> adaptor(buffer);

    // Create a binary_stream from the buffer_adaptor
    hexi::binary_stream<decltype(adaptor)> stream(adaptor);

    // Call the stream's serialise method with the packet
    stream.serialise(packet);

    // Return the buffer containing the serialized data
    return buffer;
}
```

## Explanation:

1. **NetworkPacket::serialise method**:
   - `stream << packet_id`: Writes the packet ID as a POD type (4 bytes)
   - `stream << hexi::prefixed(username)`: Writes the username with a length prefix (4-byte little-endian count followed by string data)
   - `stream << hexi::prefixed(scores)`: Writes the scores vector with a length prefix (4-byte little-endian count followed by each uint32_t score)
   - `stream << hexi::null_terminated(metadata)`: Writes the metadata as a null-terminated string (string data followed by null terminator)

2. **serialize_packet function**:
   - Creates an empty `std::vector<uint8_t>` as the underlying buffer
   - Wraps the vector with `hexi::buffer_adaptor` to provide the required buffer interface
   - Creates a `hexi::binary_stream` using the buffer adaptor
   - Calls `stream.serialise(packet)` to serialize the entire packet structure
   - Returns the populated buffer containing the serialized binary data

This implementation follows all the specified requirements and uses the Hexi library components correctly according to the reference materials.

